Weekly Progress Report
Name: Mantasha Md Anish Shaikh
Domain:Industrial Manufacturing and Production
Date of submission:04/05/2026
Week Ending: 04
I. Overview:
This week focused on understanding real-world industrial datasets related to mining and
manufacturing processes. Work was done on two major projects: Quality Prediction in a
Mining Process and Multi-stage Continuous Flow Manufacturing Process.
The primary objective was to analyze process data, understand feature relationships, and
prepare datasets for predictive modeling. Special attention was given to time-series data,
process variables, and industrial sensor data.
II. Achievements:
1. Project Familiarization:
Understood the flotation process used in mining industries.
Learned how silica impurity affects ore quality and production efficiency.
Studied continuous manufacturing systems with parallel and series machine stages.
Identified key variables affecting output quality in both datasets.
2. Python Project Contributions:
Project 10: Quality Prediction in Mining Process
Loaded dataset with time-based sampling (20 sec + hourly data).
Performed data cleaning (missing values, timestamp formatting).
Identified important features affecting silica percentage.
Conducted correlation analysis between Iron Concentrate and Silica.
Prepared dataset for predictive modeling (target: % Silica Concentrate).
Project 11: Continuous Manufacturing Process
Understood multi-stage process (Machines 1–5).
Analyzed parallel + series workflow structure.
Explored sensor measurements from 15 locations.
Preprocessed high-frequency (1 Hz) industrial data.
Identified primary and secondary output prediction targets.
